From 3307f3ecb5dd0c55336f4105a7d440b40adb33fe Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: test-k8s patch applier <test-k8s-patches@users.noreply.github.com>
Date: Tue, 17 Mar 2026 06:58:35 -0400
Subject: [PATCH] test/integration/dra: avoid duplicate sequential sharing
 stress

TestDRA still runs ShareResourceClaimSequentially in both the GA and all configurations. The test does not depend on GA-only behavior, and the duplicate invocation adds package wall time without expanding the behavior being exercised.

Upstream DRA integration tests were split across multiple files, so the old test-k8s patch no longer applies at its previous location. Rebase the same narrow change onto test/integration/dra/dra.go by keeping the sequential-sharing stress case only in the richer all configuration.

This reduces package wall time on slower CI runners without changing product behavior.

Tested: go test ./test/integration/dra -run '^$' -count=1
---
 test/integration/dra/dra.go | 3 ++-
 1 file changed, 2 insertions(+), 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/test/integration/dra/dra.go b/test/integration/dra/dra.go
index 35ce2cc6daf..3e474bdc346 100644
--- a/test/integration/dra/dra.go
+++ b/test/integration/dra/dra.go
@@ -159,7 +159,8 @@ func run(tCtx ktesting.TContext, whatRE string) {
 					tCtx = tCtx.WithNamespace(namespace)
 					TestCreateResourceSlices(tCtx, 100)
 				})
-				runSubTest(tCtx, "ShareResourceClaimSequentially", testShareResourceClaimSequentially)
+				// The same sequential-sharing stress path runs in the "all" scenario.
+				// Keep only one copy to reduce package wall time on slower CI runners.
 				runSubTest(tCtx, "UsesAllResources", testUsesAllResources)
 			},
 		},
-- 
